<speech id="uk.org.publicwhip/wms/2005-02-08.73WS.2" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/962" speakername="Keith Hill" speakeroffice="The Minister for Housing and Planning" colnum="73WS"  url="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200405/cmhansrd/cm050208/wmstext/50208m01.htm#50208m01.html_spmin0">
	<p pid=".73WS.2/1">Further to my previous statement on <phrase class="date" code="2004-12-02">2 December 2004</phrase>, <phrase class="offrep" id="wms/2004-12-02.50"><i>Official Report</i>, column 50WS</phrase>, I announce today that the Greater London authority general grant for 2005&ndash;06 has been determined at &pound;37,493,000, after consultation with the Mayor of London.</p>
	<p pid=".73WS.2/2">GLA general grant is a block grant paid for the purposes of the authority and its functional bodies.</p>
	<p pid=".73WS.2/3">I would also like to draw the Houses attention to a printing error that occurred in the <i>Official Report</i> in my previous statement. The correct figures for the GLA general grant for the following periods are as follows: &pound;37,493,000&mdash;2005&ndash;06, &pound;37,868,000&mdash;2006&ndash;07, and &pound;38,243,000&mdash;2007&ndash;08. I am sorry for any confusion caused.</p>
</speech>
